Package com.safenetinc.luna.provider.param

Contains classes that provide various algorithm parameters for the Luna JCE implementation.

See:
          Description

Class Summary
LunaAlgorithmParameterGeneratorDSA Engine class for generating DSA key parameters.
LunaECDHParameterSpec Specifies the parameters necessary for ECDH key derivation.
LunaECIESParameterSpec Specifies the parameters necessary for ECIES encryption/decryption This class is designed to be fairly neutral so that it can be replaced by a Java-native GcmParameterSpec if one appears.
LunaGcmParameterSpec Specifies the parameters necessary for GCM mode of authenticated encryption.
LunaGmacParameterSpec Specifies the parameters necessary for GMAC mode of tag generation.
LunaParametersDSA An algorithm parameters engine class for DSA parameters

LunaParametersOAEP An algorithm parameters engine class for OAEP parameters
LunaParameterSpecOAEP A parameter spec for OAEP parameters There is actually very little flexibility in the OAEP parameter specification.
LunaParametersPSS An algorithm parameters engine class for OAEP parameters
LunaParametersRC2 An algorithm parameters engine class for RC2 parameters
LunaParametersRC5 An algorithm parameter engine class for RC5 parameters
